tmux # To start tmux:

Ctrl-b d # To detach from tmux:

tmux attach # To restore tmux session:

tmux attach -d # To detach an already attached session (great if you are moving devices with different screen resolutions):

tmux ls # To display session:

Ctrl-b $ # To rename session:

Ctrl-b s # To switch session:

# To start a shared session:
tmux -S /tmp/your_shared_session
chmod 777 /tmp/your_shared_session

Ctrl-b ? # To help screen (Q to quit):

Ctrl-b PageUp/PageDown # To scroll in window:

Ctrl-b : source-file /path/to/file # To reload configuration file

Ctrl-b c # To create a window:

Ctrl-b n # To go next window:

Ctrl-b x # To destroy a window:

# To switch between windows:
Ctrl-b [0-9]
Ctrl-b Arrows

Ctrl-b % # To split windows horizontally:

Ctrl-b " # To split windows vertically:

Ctrl-b :swap-window -s [0-9] -t [0-9] # To swap windows:

# Copy and Paste in Tmux

1. Enter 'copy mode' by pressing Ctrl-b [
2. Use the arrow keys to go to the position from where you want to start copying. Press SPACE to start copying.
	2a. You should see the text being highlighted as your cursor moves.
3. Use arrow keys to go to the end of text you want to copy and press ENTER
4. Press Ctrl-b ] to paste in a possibly different Tmux pane/window.


